Source:  Sea Anglers' Fishes of NZ
Author:  PARROTT
Vol / Page:  45
Edition:
Quote:  HAKE <i>Merluccius australis</i> (Hutton) ... This New Zealand species was for many years considered to be identical with a closely allied species originally described in 1847 from Chile, and is frequently referred to in the New Zealand literature as <i>Merluccius gayi</i> .

<i>ibid.</i> 169 Hake <i>Merlangius australis</i> Whiting; Haddock
