Date:  0/0/1986
Source:  NZ Fishes: An identification Guide
Author:  PAUL
Vol / Page:  60
Edition:
Quote:  Hake <i>Merluccius australis</i> ... Also occurs off South America. Sometimes called English hake, from a similarity to a north-east Atlantic species; ... Quite different from the unrelated gemfish, but sometimes confused by the erroneous use of `hake' for gemfish in some localities.
